items.name: YoinkoorAnimeXL
items.description:
This model is an ensemble with various models(10+) on various weights and methods, this is the first version of it.
This model is great at anime style art. But cannot produce genitalia.

It works well with LoRAs and ControlNet while maintaining style at higher weights.

There are two models available for download, the FP32 model which is ~12.7 GB,

An FP16 version which is ~6.4 GB, loads faster, but comes with minute variations in details compared to the unquantized model. (might be less accurate)

Try it out here without downloading:

https://tensor.art/models/628619084524845515?source_id=nzy-oFjhnUmzp_cob3v88xki

Automatic1111

Use hiresfix x1.5 latent upscale 1.5 and high denoise 0.45-0.65.

comfyUI

Use the sdxl_refiner+hiresfix workflow to make the outputs 10 times better.

Though, I did not upscale in most of the examples.

Also try to use danbooru tags when proompting.

Share your results here, I will feature them if they are better than the current cover.

This is an SDXL LoRA. For the SD1.5 equivalent, see here: https://civitai.com/models/130057/princess-dress

Over-the-top princess dresses with lots of ruffles, volume and adornments.

Play around and create some amazing designs!

items.name: Hyperballs
items.description:
Redefines most "testicles" to be softball sized at the very least. My goal was to allow for bigger testicle sizes and more contrast between testicle and penis sizes since most futanari-centric models are already primed for huge and hyper-sized penises.

"huge testicles" is intended to make the combined size of the testicles as large as the character.

"gigantic testicles" is intended to make them larger than the character, possibly going off the frame.

Of course, YMMV with the model, lora weight and emphasis used. Trained on NAI animefull, lower the lora weight if it's frying on your merge.

Has penis size tagging so that umprompted penis size will be strictly smaller than the testicles, but you can try for larger sizes. "small penis", "huge penis" and "hyper penis" were used.

Try the following:

"sagging testicles" - self explanatory

"testicles on ground", "testicles on floor" - Should help shape testicles resting on a surface (typically the ground)

"hyperballs" used to be the activation word common to the entire dataset but I'm having better results without it.

Trained at 576x576, will gen okay up to 640. At larger resolutions you're better off upscaling a smaller picture at 0.4~0.6 denoising.

Version 2_3

  • Trained for significantly more steps (~3x)

  • Significant bump in dropout and scale weight norms. Should burn up less on other checkpoints.

  • More exhaustive tagging, resulting in better discretization of testicle sizes.

  • Token increase in training set (~15 images) to patch up blind spots

  • Downsized with sv_ratio 20. 25% of the size, 99.89% of the data

  • "squishyballs" - Experimental tag which was used on pictures where the testicles are visibly deformed from being pressed against something (a limb, a surface, the ground, etc). Too few images for it to have a significant impact but I found it lessens the instances of melding legs.

  • "balls behind" - Experimental tag to specify that the testicles should be located behind the thighs. Too gacha to be reliable but it's there.

Like its previous iteration, it works best on Futanari Alpha. It also found moderate success on Based65, and surprisingly Perfect World (despite being an ostensibly anime model). Works at 1.0, you might need to lower it on less compatible checkpoints and emphasize keywords instead.

Issues

  • Still not as widely applicable as I'd like across different models, but it's definitely a step up.

  • Scuffs faces real bad. It is not a problem for me since my routine involves upscaling from resolutions adjacent to 576x576, which fixes it for the most part, but its something to keep in mind. I recommend halving the strength you're using before upscaling.

  • Some models such as the AbyssOrange mixes have a tight stranglehold on "testicles", and it might not have an effect there. You might have to use "huge testicles" instead and play with emphasis.

items.name: Potatomash
items.description:
I used around 50 models so far in extense. I gathered some to make something that I could beat and shape to my tastes. It is a mash! But how much from what? Well, I will soon have updated the recipe and link to the models involved (which is also a requirement to credit the others.)

  • Sometimes the hands and faces get problematic and sometimes perfect. In any case I'd advise the use of the Bad Prompt embedding (with any model really) and Unspeakable Horrors one. Aside from that there is a bunch of embedding, lora and lycos out there to fix hands. I tried a lot and I can advise some if you have trouble. And about the faces you could try the face restoration feature on generation but I am not experienced on it and haven't tried it myself to share any results since It mostly does an alright job without it.

  • You can check the prompts I used, sampler, steps etc. but I should say that I prefer using Siax upscaler (I don't think it is shown on the site but you could view the image to see details) I recently did a comparison/guide but noticed that there was already one in depth so I obliterated that one.

  • Don't forget to use with any VAE, if you don't know about it just search for it on the site and pick the top (most popular ones or pick the one on files section of this page), that is what I used here but there are other ones which might even do a better job. I used Clip skip 2 on generating the images but don't have much knowledge about, it is a technical adjustment I assume so there is that too if you need to know. (I have tried it myself, it does a better job but I couldn't grasp why?) *Also use more steps for the sampler, it could give better results but might take more time generating. (Thanks to digitalghosts for pointing that out.)

Good luck with your creations! It is my first model so don't be too hard on me. Thanks!

items.name: Karlach (Baldur's Gate 3 | BG3) | LoCon
items.description:
The Barbarian Tiefling from Hell, Karlach from the game Baldur's Gate 3. Works best on 0.8-1.0. Training done on NAI.

This is a LoCon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5+ so make sure to update otherwise place in Lycoris folder.

Trigger: "Karlach, demon girl, colored skin" always needed, for accuracy add "slit pupils, scars, muscular".

Suggestions:

  • As you can change up outfits in the game her outfit varies but combinations of "crop top, black pants" can get a similar look to some of here in-game gear.

  • Add "earrings, piercings" as needed/wanted.

  • Some alternate angles and poses can break her skin, horns, tattoos and body texture due to lack of data but will still appear with some inconsistencies.

    • "Red skin, dark skin" can help with some models that handle colored skin poorly.

My favorite character from Baldur's Gate 3 so far who deserved some LoRA based love so I gave it a good shot given the lack of good images/fan-art. I will be updating this LoRA once there is a bit of extra images to work with. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.name: Bleached Jeans
items.description:
This is a 50% cosine merge between toonify_v10 + cartunafied_v3 that produces bleached images that remind me of old cartoons on a CRT television. Model A and B are the same merge with cosineA or cosineB. A produces a little bit more intricate images and B a bit more cute pictures. Both are pretty stable.

The bleached effect is mainly caused by the lack of VAE. Use anything-v4.0.vae.pt or orangemix.vae.pt to remove washed out color.

items.name: Bees! [Fluffyrock LoRA]
items.description:
(Insert Bee Movie script here)

This was actually what got me into LoRA making in the first place, and honestly, it looks great!

Trained with fluffyrock with 10 epochs and 10000 steps (using batch size of 2, which would be 5000)

The main trigger word is bee, but i'd also use black markings, yellow body, and antennas too!

(Some issues to be aware of:)

Has problems with attennaes, sometimes it gives more than 2, or less than 2.

Doesn't always give the striped pattern, hoping to fix that in future updates.

Usually gives thick thighs and wide hips, this is due to the dataset, so i'd use them in the negative prompts

Sometimes gives white borders, again, use them in the negative prompts

[AMED'S RAMBLING SECTION]

It took me long enough, honestly planned to release this first, but of course due to me having issues with the first few models. I decided to wait and learn more before I tackle species specified LoRAS

Either way, enjoy! It was quite fun to do too!
